124.8	Camping	Camping	Camping is an outdoor recreational activity. The participants (known as campers) leave urban areas, their home region, or civilization and enjoy nature while spending one or several nights outdoors, usually at a campsite. Camping may involve the use of a tent, caravan, motorhome, cabin, a primitive structure, or no shelter at all. In many parts of the world , 'camping' refers exclusively to the use of tents or similar portable structures .	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5a/Camping_by_Barriere_Lake%2C_British_Columbia_-_20040801.jpg/300px-Camping_by_Barriere_Lake%2C_British_Columbia_-_20040801.jpg
